trend_summary: Across the series, the central town edges creep outward with new housing and light-industrial plots, yet farmland still dominates. Connectivity improves along the east-west highway corridor, and scattered woodland blocks thicken slightly, hinting at greening initiatives. Overall land use shifts gently from purely agricultural to a mixed rural landscape with modest suburbanisation.
notable_changes: Incremental residential estates added on north-west and south-east fringes of the main town.
New light-industrial/warehouse rooftops appear along the highway interchange.
Field pattern alterations with several large parcels converted from crop to pasture or vice-versa.
Woodland blocks expand, especially in south-eastern quadrant, reducing open field area.
Road upgrades and small roundabouts constructed on the east-west arterial route.
